parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle pinion nut can cause the rear axle to seize or the driveshaft to separate, resulting in a loss of motive power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience vibrations
loud noises
or a sudden loss of power while driving. The rear axle may lock up
causing the vehicle to stall or lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failures can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience sudden shifts into neutral or fourth gear
hesitation while shifting
or difficulty shifting gears. The transmission may also fail to engage or disengage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience sudden loss of power
failure of the electrical system
or failure of the Totally Integrated Power Module (TIPM).

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Transmission Shift Interlock Safety Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake transmission shift interlock can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience sudden movement while in park
or the transmission may shift into gear without the driver's input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system failures can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience fuel leaks
fuel pump failure
or failure of the fuel system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle pinion nut can cause the rear axle to lock up, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The driveshaft drops to the street
breaking the transfer case
and the vehicle loses control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HVAC actuator can cause the heating and cooling system to malfunction, leading to discomfort and potential safety issues.
symptoms: Clicking noise behind the dash
AC not working
steam coming from the windshield
and the HVAC system not blowing air.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank strap can cause the fuel tank to fall off, leading to potential fires, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The fuel tank hangs loose
and the fuel strap is broken or rusted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and shifting system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle will not shift out of park
the brake pedal may or may not be pushed
and the transmission may shift out of park without a key in the ignition or brake pedal application.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch and electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The ignition switch intermittently releases the key
disconnecting all power to control and safety functions
including power steering
power brakes
lights
and airbags.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering and tie rod system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The steering becomes impossible
the vehicle pulls to the left
and the tie rod breaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sunroof can cause water to leak into the vehicle, leading to electrical issues and damage to the interior.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle through the sunroof
causing damage to the interior and electrical systems.
